    {
        ", considerable debate took place in Rome on the question as to whether to accept the Mamertines appeal for help and thus likely enter into a war with Carthage. The Romans did not wish to come to the aid of soldiers who had unjustly stolen a city from its rightful possessors, and they were still recovering from the insurrection of ": null
