        " was appointed commander of a military expedition with orders to cross to Messana. ; . Polybius. The Histories, .            Sicily is a hilly volcanic island, with geographical obstacles and rough terrain making lines of communication difficult to maintain. For this reason, land warfare played a secondary role in the First Punic War. Land operations were confined to small scale raids and skirmishes, with few ": null
