    {
        ", the Romans marched south and in turn besieged Syracuse. Polybius. The Histories, . After a brief siege, with no Carthaginian help in sight, Syracuse made peace with the Romans. .     According to the terms of the treaty, Syracuse would become a Roman ally, pay a somewhat light indemnity of 100 ": null
