        ". . Another possibility is that Rome received technical assistance from its seafaring Sicilian ally, Syracuse. Regardless of the state of their naval technology at the start of the war, Rome quickly adapted. .             In order to compensate for the lack of experience, and to make use of standard land military tactics at sea, . the Romans equipped their new ships with a special ": null
